snippet.textDisplay:
I don’t like the depiction of nilfgaard as some campy, stereotypical fantasy BAD GUY faction. One of the most intriguing elements of the witcher is that there isn’t truly one GOOD or BAD group, it is all very subjective. When you clearly align Geralt with the Shiny good boi faction and make him protect some young maiden against the black leather-clad, LOTR ORC WEAPON wielding bad guy faction who, I might add, is shown to be too angry to use cavalry, you grossly simplify the appeal of the Witcher Universe. Geralt exists in a world of political intrigue and deception, trying to balance his profession, his love for his close friends, and his indifference to most of the problems of the world around him UNLESS he is paid (depending on how you play Geralt, this may not be the case all the time. However, it is clear that Geralt switches factional allegiance or helps all parties provided he is personally motivated to do so).

This has been a rant. I’m anticipating this series lacking the soul I want it to have, hope it gets better
